## Search optimization

**scriptbots-render/src/lib.rs** (+539 lines):

Added `category_has_matches()` method for efficient category filtering during search.

**Problem**: Previously all categories rendered regardless of search, wasting computation
on categories with no matching parameters.

**Solution** (lines ~1717-2191):
```rust
fn category_has_matches(&self, category: ConfigCategory) -> bool {
    if self.settings_panel.search_query.is_empty() {
        return true; // No search - show all
    }

    // Reconstruct params for category and check matches
    match category {
        ConfigCategory::World => {
            let params = [...];
            self.has_matching_params(&params)
        }
        // ... all 10 categories
    }
}
```

**Trade-off**: Duplicates param construction logic (clarity over DRY). Alternative would
be to refactor param rendering to always construct data structures first, but current
approach is simpler and avoids API changes.

**Helper** (lines ~1707-1714):
```rust
fn has_matching_params(&self, params: &[(&str, String, &str)]) -> bool {
    if self.settings_panel.search_query.is_empty() {
        return true;
    }
    params.iter().any(|(label, value, desc)| {
        self.matches_search(label) || self.matches_search(value) || self.matches_search(desc)
    })
}
```

Future use: Can conditionally render category headers only if category has matches,
reducing UI clutter during search.

